{"parentUuid":"126dbaca-2662-453b-afa3-9fa3c8cea6ed","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a4259eb0c6d14dbce","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011Ccs78bt266hrrLsYWUqds","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_018CPVUVwWx4L2a53k25FhDv","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"cd \"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\" && cat .pipeline/debug-notes.md 2>/dev/null | tail -100"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":26160,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":26160,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":4,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccs78askCj6qVirnpwQaZ","attributionAgent":"testing","type":"assistant","uuid":"5f26d385-1d28-4ebb-904a-44e6ba94f7e7","timestamp":"2026-07-09T20:22:11.773Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
{"parentUuid":"5f26d385-1d28-4ebb-904a-44e6ba94f7e7","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a4259eb0c6d14dbce","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011Ccs78bt266hrrLsYWUqds","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_016EgjmQEg1p8SJPe1ntghZ1","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"cd \"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\" && cat .pipeline/acceptance.md 2>/dev/null | grep -n -i \"AC16\\|p95\\|export\" "},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":26160,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":282,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":26160},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":282,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":26160,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":26160,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccs78askCj6qVirnpwQaZ","attributionAgent":"testing","type":"assistant","uuid":"df41c83a-60fa-40bb-a9a3-3e489c7a9845","timestamp":"2026-07-09T20:22:12.246Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
{"parentUuid":"5f26d385-1d28-4ebb-904a-44e6ba94f7e7","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"795b6292-899f-43d1-822d-8e0cc35d6b7d","agentId":"a4259eb0c6d14dbce","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018CPVUVwWx4L2a53k25FhDv","type":"tool_result","content":"### Root cause — measured, not assumed (the disclosure was only partly right)\nI profiled each layer of the path in isolation (scratch benchmarks, 100k rows):\n\n| Layer measured in isolation | time |\n|---|---|\n| Pure CSV encoding (escape+format+writerow, no I/O) | ~360 ms |\n| ...of which `escape_csv_text_cell`'s per-char generator + `_is_safe_character` + `ord()` | ~2.4M genexpr / 2.2M `ord` calls — the encoding hot spot |\n| Real `stream_export_csv` async generator consumed directly (fake in-mem DB) | ~387 ms |\n| Through a **bare** StreamingResponse + ASGITransport (no middleware, fake DB) | ~441 ms |\n| Real DB server-side cursor draining 100k rows (no CSV, no HTTP), default fetch | ~1,014 ms |\n| ...same, with `yield_per=5000` | ~609 ms |\n| Full real `stream_export_csv` on the real DB, **minimal** Starlette app (no middleware) | ~1,644 ms |\n| ...the same path with **4 nested pass-through `BaseHTTPMiddleware`** layers added | **~6,944 ms** |\n\nThe server-side `request.completed` log confirmed the handler *returns* in 16–94 ms;\nthe ~10 s is spent **after** the handler returns, in the streaming phase.\n\n**The dominant cost is the CHUNK-PER-ROW streaming pattern, not encoding.** The\ngenerator did `yield _drain(buffer)` **per row** → 100,001 chunks at the cap. The\napp stack (`src/main.py`) has **four nested Starlette `BaseHTTPMiddleware`**\nsubclasses (`RequestContextMiddleware`, `SecurityHeadersMiddleware`,\n`BodySizeLimitMiddleware`, `Tier1EdgeThrottleMiddleware`).\n`BaseHTTPMiddleware` re-pumps **every** streamed chunk through its own anyio\nmemory-object-stream; with 4 nested layers, all 100k tiny chunks traverse 4\nanyio hops each, with async scheduling per hop. Cost ≈ (chunk count × middleware\nlayers), so it exploded at the cap. Encoding (~360 ms) and DB drain (~1 s) were\nsecondary. The implementation's disclosure conflated the fast COUNT + bounded\nsort (genuinely fast) with the row-*drain* + per-chunk-fan-out cost.\n\n### Fix — minimal, localized, WITHIN the human-approved design\nServer-side cursor, pre-flight COUNT, 100k cap, and OWASP formula-escape\nsemantics all preserved. Three complementary in-scope optimizations:\n\n1. **`src/services/usage_export_service.py` — batch rows per chunk** (`_ROWS_PER_CHUNK\n   = 1000`) instead of one chunk per row. Header still yielded first as its own\n   chunk (AC12 empty-result / AC9 first-bytes). At the cap this is ~101 chunks,\n   not 100,001 — still genuinely streamed, still constant memory (buffer holds ≤\n   one batch). **Primary lever.**\n2. **`src/api/csv_export.py` — precompiled escape.** Replaced the per-character\n   Python strip loop in `escape_csv_text_cell` with a C-level `str.translate`\n   deletion table. Semantics **identical** (verified 0 mismatches across all\n   codepoints 0x00–0x11F and lead/mid combos vs. the old logic, and by the\n   unchanged AC10 tests). Encoding 360 → 246 ms.\n3. **`src/repositories/usage_repo.py` — `yield_per=5000`** on the `session.stream()`\n   server-side cursor. Tunes how many rows are fetched per round-trip; does NOT\n   abandon the cursor. Controlled tight-loop DB drain 1,014 → 609 ms; memory\n   still bounded (≤ one batch buffered client-side).\n\n### Proven\n- **Regression test (fails-before / passes-after):**\n  `tests/test_usage_export_service.py::test_stream_export_csv_batches_rows_into_few_chunks`\n  — a 5,000-row export must arrive in < 500 chunks (batched) **and** > 1 chunk\n  (still streamed), with byte-identical CSV. Per-row impl produced 5,001 chunks\n  (**fails**); batched impl produces 6 (**passes**). Fails-before confirmed via a\n  scratch reproduction of the per-row logic (real tree never reverted);\n  passes-after **12/12** consecutive runs (deterministic, no DB/timing).\n- **No suite regressions:** `test_csv_export.py` + `test_usage_export_service.py`\n  + `test_schemas_usage_export.py` = **37 passed**; `test_usage_export_endpoint.py`\n  + `test_usage_export_perf.py` = **20 passed** (AC2/AC5–AC13/AC17/AC19/AC20/AC22\n  incl. AC9 streaming-multiple-chunks and AC10 formula-escape all green with\n  batching + the escape refactor).\n\n### Before / after p95 at the 100,000-row cap (real perf test, full app stack)\n- **BEFORE:** 10,720.92 ms (this session) / 25,210 ms (testing's independent measure)\n- **AFTER (all 3 opts):** ~1.4 s median, ~2.0 s p95 — the 2-sample perf test\n  recorded 1,454.93 ms (batching+escape) and 2,042.80 ms (all 3); a stable\n  10-sample re-measure through a 4-`BaseHTTPMiddleware` stack gave\n  **min 1,139 ms / median 1,374 ms / p95 2,073 ms**. Net: **~7–17x faster**, and\n  the chunk-per-row anti-pattern is eliminated.\n\n### Best achieved STILL exceeds 500 ms — budget decision escalates to the human\nEven after this genuine optimization pass, p95 (~1.4–2.0 s) remains above the\nplan's **proposed** 500 ms. The remainder is dominated by **irreducible work\nwithin the approved design**:\n- Draining 100k rows over the async **server-side cursor**: ~0.6 s even at\n  `yield_per=5000`. A buffered `fetchall` (which would ABANDON the mandated\n  constant-memory cursor) was ~0.32 s — so the cursor floor is already ≥0.6 s.\n- Python-level CSV encoding of 100k rows × 4 cells: ~0.25 s.\n- Even the theoretical floor that DISCARDS the cursor (fetchall 0.32 s + encoding\n  0.25 s ≈ 0.57 s) is already over 500 ms; with the mandated cursor it is ~0.85–1.0 s.\n\n**500 ms is not achievable at the 100k-row cap within the approved design**\n(server-side cursor + per-row stdlib `csv` + streaming through the\n`BaseHTTPMiddleware` stack). Per the task constraint I did **not** weaken AC16 or\nfabricate a pass — the perf test still asserts correctness and records the real\np95 (`meets_documented_budget: false`). The budget-number decision (plan Open\nQuestion 1) is the human's: confirming 500 ms as binding at the 100k cap would\nrequire a **redesign** (e.g. C-accelerated/precomputed CSV materialization, or a\nlower row cap, or moving the export off the `BaseHTTPMiddleware` request path) —\nthat is a planning-escalation question, not a patch. This remediation delivers\nthe ~7–17x reduction and removes the pathological anti-pattern; the residual\ngap to 500 ms is the escalation.\n\n### Dead ends / notes\n- First hypotheses (encoding-only; ASGI-framing-only) were **wrong** in\n  isolation — each was < 0.5 s alone. The amplifier was the middleware × chunk\n  count interaction, invisible unless the full middleware stack is in the path\n  (minimal-app benchmark showed only ~1.6 s; the 4-layer benchmark reproduced ~7 s;\n  the real app with real per-chunk middleware work + Argon2 auth reproduced ~10 s).","is_error":false}]},"uuid":"67aee21f-5c27-4dd5-89b3-c59d915a5a05","timestamp":"2026-07-09T20:22:14.347Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"5f26d385-1d28-4ebb-904a-44e6ba94f7e7","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
{"parentUuid":"df41c83a-60fa-40bb-a9a3-3e489c7a9845","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"795b6292-899f-43d1-822d-8e0cc35d6b7d","agentId":"a4259eb0c6d14dbce","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016EgjmQEg1p8SJPe1ntghZ1","type":"tool_result","content":"2:feature: usage CSV export (GET /v1/usage/export)\n9:  testing marks it covered:false, delegated:\"security\". No performance k6 load AC: the export is\n10:  a reporting route with a documented p95 sanity check (AC16); the binding perf constraint is the\n18:| AC1 | Response is RFC 4180 CSV via stdlib `csv`: header row exactly `customer_id,metric,window_start,total_quantity` (brief column order), CRLF line endings, fields containing comma/quote/newline quoted | `src/api/csv_export.py`, `src/services/usage_export_service.py` | Unit (dialect, header, CRLF, quoting) + integration end-to-end body assertion |\n19:| AC2 | Optional `customer_id`/`metric`/`from`/`to` filters applied (reusing existing allowlist types + window bounds); all omitted → full supported range | `src/api/schemas/usage_export.py`, `src/repositories/usage_repo.py` | Unit (schema) + integration (each filter narrows the row set; none → all caller rows) |\n20:| AC3 | `from`/`to` validation: timezone-aware, `from <= to`, both within `[now-90d, now+1h]`, naive datetime rejected | `src/api/schemas/usage_export.py` | Unit (accept/reject cases incl. naive, inverted range, out-of-window) |\n21:| AC4 | Input validation (non-waivable): malformed / wrong-type / unknown / out-of-range query param → 422 `validation_failed`; `extra=\"forbid\"` rejects unknown params | `src/api/schemas/usage_export.py`, `src/api/errors.py` | Unit + integration (422 envelope with `code=validation_failed`) |\n22:| AC5 | Rate limit: post-auth **Tier-2 per-`api_key_id`** throttle applies (principal-keyed); two principals on one client IP get independent buckets | `src/api/routes/usage_export.py` (reuses `src/auth/rate_limit.py`) | Integration two-principals-one-IP discriminating test |\n23:| AC6 | Authorization: any authenticated key (ingest or admin) may export; unauthenticated/invalid → 401; no scope gate | `src/api/routes/usage_export.py`, `src/auth` | Integration (ingest key 200, admin key 200, no/invalid key 401) |\n24:| AC7 | Tenant isolation: export returns ONLY the caller's `api_key_id` rows; two tenants' data never cross (explicit `api_key_id` filter is the primary control; RLS is backstop) | `src/repositories/usage_repo.py` | Integration two-tenant test (tenant A's export excludes tenant B's rows) |\n25:| AC8 | Row cap: a result exceeding 100,000 rows → 422 `validation_failed` (\"narrow filters\"), **no partial body streamed** (pre-flight count before any response byte) | `src/services/usage_export_service.py`, `src/repositories/usage_repo.py` | Integration (>100k rows → 422, response body is the envelope not CSV) |\n26:| AC9 | Streaming constant memory: rows streamed as read via a server-side cursor, response not fully buffered before send | `src/services/usage_export_service.py` | Integration streaming-not-buffered sanity (first bytes observable before generator exhausted / bounded memory on a large export) |\n27:| AC10 | CSV formula-injection escape: text cells (`customer_id`,`metric`) starting with `= + - @ \\t \\r` prefixed with `'`; control chars neutralized; numeric/timestamp cells untouched | `src/api/csv_export.py` | Unit (incl. leading-`-` `customer_id`, each trigger, control chars, numeric/timestamp unaffected) + integration end-to-end |\n28:| AC11 | Response headers: `Content-Type: text/csv; charset=utf-8`; `Content-Disposition: attachment; filename=usage-export-<UTC timestamp>.csv` (no tenant identifier in filename); inherits `nosniff` + `Cache-Control: no-store` | `src/api/routes/usage_export.py`, `src/api/middleware.py` | Integration header assertions (incl. filename pattern, no tenant id) |\n29:| AC12 | Empty result → 200 header-only CSV (single header row, zero data rows), never 404 | `src/services/usage_export_service.py` | Integration (caller with no matching rollups → 200, one CSV line) |\n30:| AC13 | Deterministic ordering `ORDER BY window_start, customer_id, metric ASC`; identical exports are byte-stable | `src/repositories/usage_repo.py` | Integration (asserts row order over a seeded multi-row set) |\n31:| AC14 | Value formats: `window_start` as UTC ISO-8601 with offset (identical to JSON response form); `total_quantity` as `str(Decimal)` (plain decimal, no scientific notation) | `src/api/csv_export.py`, `src/services/usage_export_service.py` | Unit + integration (format assertions) |\n33:| AC16 | Performance budget: export route **p95 <= 3,000 ms at the 100,000-row cap** (integration timing sanity — NOT a k6 load AC). *[Human-confirmed at the 2026-07-09 debugging escalation, resolving plan Open Q1: the proposed 500 ms is unreachable within the approved constant-memory streaming design (irreducible ~0.85–1.0 s cursor+encoding floor; optimized p95 2.07 s stable at the cap). 500 ms would require a design change (buffered fetch or lower cap) and is recorded as aspiration, not budget.]* | `src/services/usage_export_service.py`, `src/repositories/usage_repo.py` | Integration timing sanity test at ~100k rows asserting the <= 3,000 ms bound |\n34:| AC17 | Audit logging: exactly one `usage.export` `info` event at completion (`userId`=opaque `api_key_id`, `operation`, `rowCount`, `capped`, `completed`, filter-presence booleans — no raw `customer_id`); over-cap request logged at `warn` | `src/services/usage_export_service.py`, `src/logging` | Unit/integration (log fields present, no PII, one event; `warn` on over-cap) |\n36:| AC19 (DAST-1) | Served OpenAPI schema includes `GET /v1/usage/export` with its `200 text/csv` and `422` responses, matching the implemented route (not hand-drifted) | `src/api/routes/usage_export.py` | Integration (assert route + responses present in `/openapi.json`) |\n37:| AC20 (DAST-2) | A seeded non-production DAST test key (reuse the existing seeded key; credentials from env/secrets, never hardcoded) can call the export | `scripts/seed_api_key.py` (existing), test fixtures | Integration (seeded key successfully hits the export in staging/local) |\n39:| AC22 | Safe-error / fail-closed pre-flight: a forced internal error during the pre-flight `prepare_export` `COUNT` phase (before any response byte) returns the generic `500 internal` error-envelope (no stack/SQL/internal path leaked), rolls back the transaction, and starts **no** stream / emits **no** partial CSV body (ASVS 16.5.x). Distinct from plan §R3 (post-200 mid-stream truncation, accepted) | `src/services/usage_export_service.py`, `src/api/errors.py`, `src/api/routes/usage_export.py` | Unit in `tests/test_usage_export_service.py` (non-cap DB error propagates, not swallowed, no stream started) + integration in `tests/integration/test_usage_export_endpoint.py` (forced pre-flight `COUNT` error → `500 internal` envelope, no leak, no partial body) |","is_error":false}]},"uuid":"3756ce84-a599-4aa5-b01a-2df013398417","timestamp":"2026-07-09T20:22:15.619Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"df41c83a-60fa-40bb-a9a3-3e489c7a9845","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
