metric_filter_narrows_the_result, test_export_from_to_window_filter_narrows_the_result, test_export_with_no_filters_returns_all_caller_rows\",\r\n        \"reason\": \"each filter independently narrows the row set; all-omitted returns full set\"\r\n      },\r\n      {\r\n        \"id\": \"AC3\",\r\n        \"covered\": true,\r\n        \"test\": \"tests/test_schemas_usage_export.py::test_from_alias_binds_to_from__field, test_rejects_naive_from_datetime, test_rejects_naive_to_datetime, test_rejects_from_after_to, test_accepts_from_equal_to_to, test_rejects_from_too_far_in_the_past, test_rejects_to_too_far_in_the_future\",\r\n        \"reason\": \"naive-reject, inverted-range-reject, and both window-bound edges (90d/1h) exercised\"\r\n      },\r\n      {\r\n        \"id\": \"AC4\",\r\n        \"covered\": true,\r\n        \"test\": \"tests/test_schemas_usage_export.py::test_rejects_injection_in_customer_id, test_rejects_unknown_fields; tests/integration/test_usage_export_endpoint.py::test_export_malformed_query_param_returns_422, test_export_unknown_query_param_returns_422\",\r\n        \"reason\": \"422 envelope + extra=forbid verified at unit and integration tiers\"\r\n      },\r\n      {\r\n        \"id\": \"AC5\",\r\n        \"covered\": true,\r\n        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_usage_export_endpoint.py::test_export_rate_limit_two_principals_one_ip_get_independent_buckets\",\r\n        \"reason\": \"discriminating two-principals-one-IP shape (not the weak same-owner-only form) proves the Tier-2 throttle is keyed on api_key_id, not client IP\"\r\n      },\r\n      {\r\n        \"id\": \"AC6\",\r\n        \"covered\": true,\r\n        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_usage_export_endpoint.py::test_export_requires_authentication, test_export_any_authenticated_scope_may_export_ingest_and_admin\",\r\n        \"reason\": \"no/invalid key -> 401; both ingest- and admin-scoped keys -> 200 (no scope gate)\"\r\n      },\r\n      {\r\n        \"id\": \"AC7\",\r\n        \"covered\": true,\r\n        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_usage_export_endpoint.py::test_export_tenant_isolation_excludes_other_tenants_rows\",\r\n        \"reason\": \"IDOR/BOLA shape: two tenants share a customer_id value; tenant A's export excludes tenant B's row by value, not just by count\"\r\n      },\r\n      {\r\n        \"id\": \"AC8\",\r\n        \"covered\": true,\r\n        \"test\": \"tests/test_usage_export_service.py::test_prepare_export_passes_when_exactly_at_cap_boundary (added this session), test_prepare_export_rejects_over_cap_with_422; tests/integration/test_usage_export_endpoint.py::test_export_row_cap_returns_422_with_no_partial_body\",\r\n        \"reason\": \"both sides of the boundary now covered (exactly-at-cap passes, cap+1 rejects) plus the no-partial-body integration proof\"\r\n      },\r\n      {\r\n        \"id\": \"AC9\",\r\n        \"covered\": true,\r\n        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_usage_export_endpoint.py::test_export_streaming_delivers_multiple_discrete_chunks\",\r\n        \"reason\": \"genuine socket-level chunk-boundary proof via an out-of-process uvicorn server (the in-process ASGITransport was independently verified unusable for this by implementation and re-confirmed by reading the fixture and its cited httpx internals)\"\r\n      },\r\n      {\r\n        \"id\": \"AC10\",\r\n        \"covered\": true,\r\n        \"test\": \"tests/test_csv_export.py::test_leading_formula_trigger_is_quote_prefixed, test_leading_dash_customer_id_is_escaped, test_embedded_control_characters_are_stripped; tests/integration/test_usage_export_endpoint.py::test_export_formula_injection_is_escaped_end_to_end\",\r\n        \"reason\": \"every OWASP trigger char parametrized at unit tier, plus the reachable leading-dash case end-to-end\"\r\n      },\r\n      {\r\n        \"id\": \"AC11\",\r\n        \"covered\": true,\r\n        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_usage_export_endpoint.py::test_export_response_headers\",\r\n        \"reason\": \"content-type, filename regex (no tenant id), nosniff, no-store all asserted; filename pinned to a full regex, not a substring exclusion\"\r\n      },\r\n      {\r\n        \"id\": \"AC12\",\r\n        \"covered\": true,\r\n        \"test\": \"tests/test_usage_export_service.py::test_stream_export_csv_is_header_only_on_empty_result; tests/integration/test_usage_export_endpoint.py::test_export_is_header_only_csv_for_empty_result\",\r\n        \"reason\": \"200 header-only CSV verified at unit and integration tiers, never 404\"\r\n      },\r\n      {\r\n        \"id\": \"AC13\",\r\n        \"covered\": true,\r\n        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_usage_export_endpoint.py::test_export_deterministic_ordering\",\r\n        \"reason\": \"rows inserted out of customer_id order; export asserts sorted order over a seeded multi-row set\"\r\n      },\r\n      {\r\n        \"id\": \"AC14\",\r\n        \"covered\": true,\r\n        \"test\": \"tests/test_csv_export.py::test_total_quantity_formats_as_plain_decimal_no_scientific_notation, test_window_start_formats_as_utc_iso8601_with_offset\",\r\n        \"reason\": \"format assertions at both scale-6 boundary and offset-formatting\"\r\n      },\r\n      {\r\n        \"id\": \"AC15\",\r\n        \"covered\": true,\r\n        \"test\": \"full suite run this session: tests/integration/test_events_endpoint.py, tests/integration/test_usage_endpoint.py, tests/integration/test_quotas_endpoint.py all green unchanged; verified this session via `git diff HEAD --name-only` + `git ls-files --others` that no file under alembic/versions/ was added or modified\",\r\n        \"reason\": \"negative criterion: existing endpoint suites pass unchanged and no new migration exists\"\r\n      },\r\n      {\r\n        \"id\": \"AC16\",\r\n        \"covered\": false,\r\n        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_usage_export_perf.py::test_export_p95_timing_sanity_at_the_row_cap\",\r\n        \"reason\": \"measured, not fabricated: real p95 at the 100,000-row cap is 25,210 ms against the documented 500 ms budget (~50x over) -- this run's own measurement (scratch file), independent of implementation's earlier ~9.8s figure on different hardware. The test intentionally does not hard-assert the budget (plan's Open Question 1 left it unconfirmed), but a budget this far exceeded is a genuine, reproducible finding, not a passing criterion -- left uncovered rather than marked covered by a test that never actually checks it.\"\r\n      },\r\n      {\r\n        \"id\": \"AC17\",\r\n        \"covered\": true,\r\n        \"test\": \"tests/test_usage_export_service.py::test_stream_export_csv_logs_completion_audit_event, test_prepare_export_rejects_over_cap_with_422, test_stream_export_csv_completion_is_false_on_mid_stream_failure\",\r\n        \"reason\": \"info event with rowCount/capped/completed and no raw customer_id; warn event on over-cap; completed=false on mid-stream failure\"\r\n      },\r\n      {\r\n        \"id\": \"AC18\",\r\n        \"covered\": false,\r\n        \"delegated\": \"security\",\r\n        \"test\": null,\r\n        \"reason\": \"delegated to the security stage per acceptance.md frontmatter (delegated_criteria: [AC18]) -- ASVS reconciliation, not a test-suite assertion\"\r\n      },\r\n      {\r\n        \"id\": \"AC19\",\r\n        \"covered\": true,\r\n        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_usage_export_endpoint.py::test_openapi_schema_exposes_the_export_route_and_responses\",\r\n        \"reason\": \"served /openapi.json includes the route with its 200 text/csv and 422 responses\"\r\n      },\r\n      {\r\n        \"id\": \"AC20\",\r\n        \"covered\": true,\r\n        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_usage_export_endpoint.py::test_export_seeded_dast_key_can_call_the_export (added this session)\",\r\n        \"reason\": \"the pre-existing test_seed_api_key_script.py proves the script persists a working key row but never calls any endpoint with the printed key -- this was a genuine gap; the added test runs the real seed script and calls the export route with its printed key, closing it\"\r\n      },\r\n      {\r\n        \"id\": \"AC21\",\r\n        \"covered\": true,\r\n        \"test\": \"tests/test_dast_context_documented.py::test_bearer_split_token_auth_context_is_documented (pre-existing, feature-agnostic); tests/integration/test_usage_export_endpoint.py exercises the identical Bearer mtr_live_<key_id>_<secret> shape throughout\",\r\n        \"reason\": \"inherited coverage from a pre-existing, unchanged test plus this feature's own integration tests using the same auth shape\"\r\n      },\r\n      {\r\n        \"id\": \"AC22\",\r\n        \"covered\": true,\r\n        \"test\": \"tests/test_usage_export_service.py::test_prepare_export_propagates_non_cap_error_uncaught; tests/integration/test_usage_export_endpoint.py::test_export_forced_pre_flight_count_error_returns_generic_500\",\r\n        \"reason\": \"unit proves the error is not swallowed; integration proves it maps to a generic 500 envelope (no stack/SQL/internal path) with no partial CSV body -- both distinguish this pre-flight case from the accepted post-200 mid-stream case\"\r\n      }\r\n    ]\r\n  },\r\n  \"resilience\": {\r\n    \"migration_roundtrip\": \"n/a\",\r\n    \"property_tests\": 0,\r\n    \"concurrency\": \"n/a\"\r\n  },\r\n  \"perf\": {\r\n    \"budget\": {\r\n      \"p95_ms\": 500,\r\n      \"throughput_rps\": null\r\n    },\r\n    \"measured\": {\r\n      \"p95_ms\": 25210.46,\r\n      \"throughput_rps\": null\r\n    },\r\n    \"scenario\": {\r\n      \"concurrency\": 1,\r\n      \"workload\": \"sequential export requests of the caller's full 100,000-row usage_rollup set, in-process ASGI transport against a real Postgres testcontainer\",\r\n      \"contention\": \"none -- single client, single tenant, no concurrent requests\",\r\n      \"sample_count\": 2,\r\n      \"optional_egress\": \"none (no webhook/external call on this path)\"\r\n    },\