{"parentUuid":"78723d3b-3af9-4875-a37a-b6e953dcf4e0","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"795b6292-899f-43d1-822d-8e0cc35d6b7d","agentId":"a4259eb0c6d14dbce","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01B2Fth4z3ASPqceYUQhKVMF","type":"tool_result","content":"{\n  \"quality_ok\": false,\n  \"quality_waiver\": null,\n  \"ran_at\": \"2026-07-09T19:09:38Z\",\n  \"mutation\": {\n    \"tool\": \"mutmut\",\n    \"configured_scope\": [\"src/api/csv_export.py\", \"src/services/usage_export_service.py\", \"src/api/schemas/usage_export.py\"],\n    \"scope\": [],\n    \"score\": null,\n    \"killed\": 0,\n    \"survived\": 0,\n    \"threshold\": null,\n    \"note\": \"mutmut refuses to run on native Windows (`mutmut --version` prints 'To run mutmut on Windows, please use the WSL' -- verified this session), matching the project's own CI comment that mutation testing is deliberately deferred to the Linux CI job (pipeline-ci.yml's `mutation` job, currently `if: false` pending <MUTATION_CMD>/<MUTATION_SCOPE>). Not run locally this session; scope could not be exercised at all (0 of configured_scope), so quality_ok is honestly false rather than claimed true against an unmeasured scope.\"\n  },\n  \"adversarial_review\": {\n    \"gaps\": [\n      {\n        \"area\": \"AC16 / usage_export_service.py + usage_repo.py\",\n        \"gap\": \"The suite records but does not gate on the p95 budget. Measured p95 at the cap is ~25s vs a 500ms budget (~50x over), reproduced independently this session (implementation's own run measured ~9.8s on different hardware -- both runs agree the budget is badly missed, only the magnitude differs). This is a real performance defect (per-row Python-level CSV encoding overhead across 100k rows, per implementation's own root-cause note), not a test gap per se, but the AC is correctly left uncovered in test-results.json rather than papered over.\",\n        \"severity\": \"high\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"area\": \"AC9 streaming-not-buffered\",\n        \"gap\": \"The chunk-count>1 assertion is a reasonable proxy for 'not fully buffered' but does not directly measure peak memory. A future regression that buffers the whole result client-side but still happens to flush in more than one TCP segment (e.g. due to buffering N rows at a time rather than 1) would still pass this test. A memory-ceiling assertion (e.g. tracemalloc peak during the stream) would close this more tightly.\",\n        \"severity\": \"medium\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"area\": \"usage_repo.py count_usage_rollups / stream_usage_rollups\",\n        \"gap\": \"No test exercises a combination of ALL four filters simultaneously (customer_id + metric + from + to together) -- each filter is tested in isolation. The shared `_export_filter_clause_and_params` helper makes this low-risk (the WHERE-clause construction is compositional and unit-testable by inspection), but an integration test combining all four would remove the remaining inference.\",\n        \"severity\": \"low\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"area\": \"usage_export_service.py stream_export_csv\",\n        \"gap\": \"No test drives a client disconnect mid-stream against the real integration server (running_server fixture) to observe the `completed=False` log path under real ASGI/ASGI-middleware conditions -- the unit test simulates this by raising inside a mocked generator, which proves the finally-block logic but not that Starlette's real disconnect handling reaches it the same way in production.\",\n        \"severity\": \"low\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"area\": \"usage_repo.py line 130 (count_usage_rollups' `return result.scalar_one()`)\",\n        \"gap\": \"Coverage reports this exact line as missed despite count_usage_rollups being called by many passing tests (cap-boundary, cap-exceeded, filter tests) -- worth a follow-up look (likely a coverage/line-mapping artifact from the f-string SQL literal spanning multiple source lines, not a real untested branch, but not independently confirmed this session).\",\n        \"severity\": \"low\"\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}","is_error":false}]},"uuid":"11d05887-5735-4b06-bc6f-a8c044bfef1e","timestamp":"2026-07-09T20:27:43.721Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"78723d3b-3af9-4875-a37a-b6e953dcf4e0","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
